Patterns of Inheritance 
\f1\b0\fs36 \cf4 \cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl300\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b \cf4 \cb3 Incomplete dominance 
\f1\b0 is the situation where one allele is 
\f2\i not completely expressed 
\f1\i0 over its paired allele. The heterozygous will have an 
\f0\b intermediate 
\f1\b0 state. (Ex. red x white = 
\f2\i pink
\f1\i0 ). \cb1 \

\f0\b \cb3 Codominance 
\f1\b0 is the situation where the heterozygous will express 
\f0\b both alleles
\f2\i\b0 . 
\f1\i0 (Ex. red x white = 
\f2\i red + white spots
\f1\i0 ). \cb1 \

\f0\b \cb3 Multiple alleles 
\f1\b0 describes when there are 
\f0\b more allele options 
\f1\b0 than just two. (Ex. ABO blood typing - 
\f2\i A, B, O alleles
\f1\i0 ). \cb1 \

\f0\b \cb3 Epistasis 
\f1\b0 is when one gene affects the 
\f2\i expression 
\f1\i0 of a 
\f0\b different gene
\f1\b0 . (Ex. 
\f2\i baldness 
\f1\i0 gene covers up the genes for 
\f2\i hair color
\f1\i0 ). \cb1 \

\f0\b \cb3 Pleiotropy 
\f1\b0 describes when 
\f0\b one gene 
\f1\b0 is responsible for 
\f0\b many traits
\f1\b0 . (Ex. 
\f2\i cystic fibrosis
\f1\i0 , disease with many symptoms caused by a 
\f2\i single gene
\f1\i0 ). \cb1 \

\f0\b \cb3 Polygenic inheritance 
\f1\b0 when 
\f0\b many genes 
\f1\b0 are responsible for 
\f0\b one trait
\f1\b0 . This gives the trait 
\f0\b continuous variation
\f1\b0 . (Ex. 
\f2\i height
\f1\i0 , a single trait affected by 
\f2\i many genes
\f1\i0 ). \cb1 \
