\f0\b \cb3 Aneuploidy 
\f1\b0 refers to an 
\f2\i abnormal 
\f1\i0 number of chromosomes in the daughter cells. After fertilization, 
\f0\b trisomy 
\f1\b0 (3 chromosomes copies) or 
\f0\b monosomy 
\f1\b0 (1 chromosome copies) can occur. \cb1 \

\f0\b \cb3 Down syndrome 
\f1\b0 is a trisomy of chromosome #21 (each diploid cell has 
\f2\i 47 chromosomes 
\f1\i0 total). \cb1 \

\f0\b \cb3 Turner syndrome 
\f1\b0 is a monosomy of the X chromosome in females (each diploid cell has 
\f2\i 45 chromosomes 
\f1\i0 total). Individuals have physical abnormalities and sterility. \cb1 \

\f0\b \cb3 Klinefelter\'92s syndrome 
\f1\b0 is a trisomy of the sex chromosomes in males, giving them XXY (each diploid cell has 
\f2\i 47 chromosomes 
\f1\i0 total). Individuals usually have disorders in intellectual, physical, and reproductive development. \cb1 \
